<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id90ef7ffc-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s7802"><num value="7802">§ 7802.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of this chapter are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id90ef7ffd-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s7802/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to promote respect for and protection of fundamental human rights in North Korea;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id90ef7ffe-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s7802/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to promote a more durable humanitarian solution to the plight of North Korean refugees;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id90ef7fff-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s7802/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> to promote increased monitoring, access, and transparency in the provision of humanitarian assistance inside North Korea;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id90ef8000-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s7802/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> to promote the free flow of information into and out of North Korea; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id90ef8001-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s7802/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> to promote progress toward the peaceful reunification of the Korean peninsula under a democratic system of government.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id90ef8002-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/333/s4">Pub. L. 108–333, § 4</ref>, <date date="2004-10-18">Oct. 18, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/1290">118 Stat. 1290</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
